\begin_layout Section
Exercises
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The 
\family typewriter
mosaic
\family default
 package includes a function that allows for a point and click interface
 to building a graph in 
\family typewriter
ggplot2
\family default
.
 The point of the 
\family typewriter
mplot()
\family default
 command is to allow you to do some point and click selection to build a
 graph and then click the button that produces the R commands that produced
 the graph.
 You then copy and past the R commands into your markdown file.
 Once you know the ggplot2 system better, you won’t ever bother with 
\family typewriter
mplot()
\family default
, you'll just type it in directly.
 Until then it is nice to have some help in formatting the plotting commands.
 
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
Load the 
\family typewriter
mosaic
\family default
 library.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


