\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Have 
\family typewriter
mplot()
\family default
 produce the code to produce this graph and copy that code into your RMarkdown
 file for this lab.
 Because 
\family typewriter
mplot()
\family default
 *requires* user input via the mouse, it is a pointless command for a document
 that will be printed and will cause an error when you try to knit your
 results.
 Instead you’ll use 
\family typewriter
mplot()
\family default
 to help produce the code for a graphic, and then do any final tweaking
 on the graph that is necessary.
 In your write up, I would recommend that you include the 
\family typewriter
mplot()
\family default
 command so that you can go back and remember how it was called but then
 comment it out using the ‘#’ character.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Add appropriate labels for the x and y axes along with a title.
\end_layout

